						               													<description>A tactical deckbuilder for 1-4 players, from the creator of Dragon Bridge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Set in the Gem Wizards Universe (Gem Wizards Tactics, Dragon Bridge). As in these other games, Spellstorm features the ninja bug Omar Evans, the business demon intern Derby Pocket, radical activist skeleton Eve Williams, plus a bunch of new fun characters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Spellstorm, 1-4 wizards do battle, casting a sequence of spells in order, slowly unfolding their tactics and overwhelming the opponent with powerful summons, using a never-before-seen new kind of deckbuilding system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Choose from 8 wildly asymmetrical characters with their own unique magical powers. Will you win by having a strong economy, purchasing powerful Diamonds and Dragons? Will you rush them down with red Fire cards? You'll constantly have to adapt your strategy after each battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players draft a new card between each battle, slightly shifting their strategy. During a battle, players simultaneously play a card into 4 to 6 lanes. At the end of the last lane (the number of lanes is determined by certain Spellstorm Weather effects), whichever side has more power wins and deals damage to the opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Spellstorm is a game that's easy to learn but takes years to master all of its systems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
